result.name: Kowloon City Plaza

reviews.text: Kowloon City Plaza is a typical shopping mall in a residental area of Hong Kong. It is a fancy-free very down to earth place which would not attract much attention to tourists who might look for international brand names. But tourists are not the target customers - locals are.This attraction is of little interest to a tourist . Each level of the plaza has shops of similar theme.For instance,one level is dedicated to telecommunications. Rather than having food in the plaza,venture out to one of the many eateries located on the streets nearby.
A great shopping mall for the locals.
A quiet shopping mall.

Lots of shops closed down, it's our only place to cool down in the hot summer. Need to bring in trendy hk cafe, Japanese restaurants, and Taiwanese restaurants into the mall. Would have been a dream came true to have indoor children playground, and I am not talking about the children zone that is currently at the basement.
Lots of shops with good deals, and the supermarket has a big sale each Tuesday so go there and see if you have been lucky!
